s, and the environment. It is also about a deeper movement to retain a sense of place that is Austin, and how that deeper movement continues to shape the way Austin is built today. The city it helped to create is now on the forefront of national efforts to rethink how we build our cities, reduce global warming, and find ways that humans and the environment can coexist in a big city.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 0aCity planningxEnvironmental aspectszTexaszAustin. 0aEnvironmentalismzTexaszAustin. 0aLand use, UrbanxEnvironmental aspectszTexaszAustin. 7aNATURE / Environmental Conservation & Protection.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292792784423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292792784/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK